1177
00:47:42,783 --> 00:47:44,618
A mechanism allowing survival

1178
00:47:44,653 --> 00:47:45,982
for thousands of years?

1179
00:47:46,017 --> 00:47:48,249
Run out of room even faster.

1180
00:47:48,284 --> 00:47:50,551
Then we'd have to go to Mars as a colony

1181
00:47:50,586 --> 00:47:52,451
as we expanded, as we'd have to.

1182
00:47:52,486 --> 00:47:54,382
I'd like that.

1183
00:47:54,417 --> 00:47:56,384
On a planet of another star.

1184
00:47:56,419 --> 00:47:58,249
I envy you.

1185
00:47:58,284 --> 00:48:00,616
Did you have a pet dinosaur?

1186
00:48:00,651 --> 00:48:03,017
They were a little bit before my time.

1187
00:48:03,052 --> 00:48:04,249
At least something is.

1188
00:48:04,284 --> 00:48:07,351
No doubt you could give us
a thousand details, John,

1189
00:48:07,386 --> 00:48:08,416
corroborating your story,

1190
00:48:08,451 --> 00:48:10,917
from the Magdalene to the Buddha to now.

1191
00:48:10,952 --> 00:48:12,082
Ten thousand,

1192
00:48:12,117 --> 00:48:13,718
and you could stay out of the books.

1193
00:48:13,753 --> 00:48:16,182
Oh, it's getting chilly.

1194
00:48:16,217 --> 00:48:18,417
Here, come over here. Join me.

1195
00:48:20,783 --> 00:48:24,417
That, uh, raises an
interesting question, John.

1196
00:48:24,452 --> 00:48:25,915
Could there be others like you

1197
00:48:25,950 --> 00:48:28,150
who escaped the aging
process as you have?

1198
00:48:28,185 --> 00:48:29,534
Representing something terrific

1199
00:48:29,569 --> 00:48:30,883
we don't even know about in biology.

1200
00:48:30,918 --> 00:48:32,151
We're learning all the time.

1201
00:48:32,186 --> 00:48:33,349
Yeah, but how would he know?

1202
00:48:33,384 --> 00:48:36,417
He doesn't wear an I.D. badge
saying "yabba dabba doo."

1203
00:48:36,452 --> 00:48:39,068
There was a man in the 1600s.

1204
00:48:39,103 --> 00:48:41,649
Where were you in 1292 A.D.?

1205
00:48:41,684 --> 00:48:44,284
Where were you a year ago on this date?

1206
00:48:46,950 --> 00:48:49,718
Anyway, it was the
1600s, and I met a man,

1207
00:48:49,753 --> 00:48:52,451
and I had a hunch that he was...

1208
00:48:52,486 --> 00:48:54,382
like me, so I told him.

1209
00:48:54,417 --> 00:48:58,184
Ah. See, you said this was a first.

1210
00:48:58,219 --> 00:48:59,182
I forgot.

1211
00:48:59,217 --> 00:49:01,084
A crack in your story, John?

1212
00:49:01,119 --> 00:49:03,118
A touch of senility.

1213
00:49:03,153 --> 00:49:05,082
Anyway, he said yes,

1214
00:49:05,117 --> 00:49:07,117
but from another time, another place.

1215
00:49:07,152 --> 00:49:08,649
We talked for two days.

1216
00:49:08,684 --> 00:49:10,651
It was all pretty convincing,

1217
00:49:10,686 --> 00:49:12,915
But we couldn't be sure.

1218
00:49:12,950 --> 00:49:15,217
We each confirmed what the other said,

1219
00:49:15,252 --> 00:49:17,484
but how do we know if the confirmation

1220
00:49:17,519 --> 00:49:19,284
was genuine or an echo?

1221
00:49:19,319 --> 00:49:21,015
I knew I was kosher,

1222
00:49:21,050 --> 00:49:24,950
but I thought, "maybe he's
playing a game on me."

1223
00:49:24,985 --> 00:49:28,349
You know, a scholar
of all we spoke about.

1224
00:49:28,384 --> 00:49:31,417
He said he was inclined
with the same reservation.

1225
00:49:31,452 --> 00:49:32,649
Now, that's interesting.

1226
00:49:32,684 --> 00:49:34,850
Just as we can never be sure,

1227
00:49:34,885 --> 00:49:36,434
even if we wanted to.

1228
00:49:36,469 --> 00:49:37,949
I mean, if we were sure,

1229
00:49:37,984 --> 00:49:39,649
you couldn't be sure of that.

1230
00:49:39,684 --> 00:49:41,783
We parted, agreeing to keep in touch

1231
00:49:41,818 --> 00:49:43,216
- of course, we didn't -

1232
00:49:43,251 --> 00:49:45,718
and 200 years later I thought I saw him

1233
00:49:45,753 --> 00:49:47,984
in a train station in Brussels.

1234
00:49:48,019 --> 00:49:49,551
Lost him in the crowd.

1235
00:49:49,586 --> 00:49:51,715
Oh, what a shame.

1236
00:49:51,750 --> 00:49:53,550
I- I mean, if it were true.

1237
00:49:53,585 --> 00:49:55,316
Okay, here's one for you.

1238
00:49:55,351 --> 00:49:57,651
What do you do in your spare time?

1239
00:49:58,817 --> 00:49:59,915
Every 50 years or so,

1240
00:49:59,950 --> 00:50:01,815
when I wanna get away from the rush,

1241
00:50:01,850 --> 00:50:04,234
I go down to a primitive
tribe in New Guinea

1242
00:50:04,269 --> 00:50:06,618
where I'm worshipped as an immortal god,

1243
00:50:06,653 --> 00:50:09,017
and they have a huge statue of me.

1244
00:50:09,052 --> 00:50:10,216
It's a big party.

1245
00:50:10,251 --> 00:50:12,217
Yeah, I've got a lot of pictures of it,

1246
00:50:12,252 --> 00:50:14,149
but I've already packed
them up. I'm sorry.

1247
00:50:14,184 --> 00:50:17,917
I won't make the obvious nasty
crack about more unwashed cavemen.

1248
00:50:17,952 --> 00:50:19,282
Actually, bathing was the style

1249
00:50:19,317 --> 00:50:21,184
until the middle ages
when the church told us

1250
00:50:21,219 --> 00:50:24,050
it was sinful to wash away God's dirt,

1251
00:50:24,085 --> 00:50:25,282
so people were sewn

1252
00:50:25,317 --> 00:50:26,967
into their underwear in October

1253
00:50:27,002 --> 00:50:28,709
and they popped out in April.

1254
00:50:28,744 --> 00:50:30,417
You said you just happened.

1255
00:50:30,452 --> 00:50:32,284
I don't believe that.

1256
00:50:32,319 --> 00:50:34,082
If your story's true,

1257
00:50:34,117 --> 00:50:37,033
why did God allow you to happen?

1258
00:50:37,068 --> 00:50:39,950
That makes an interesting point.

1259
00:50:39,985 --> 00:50:41,616
Are you religious, John?

1260
00:50:41,651 --> 00:50:44,184
I don't follow a known religion. No.

1261
00:50:44,219 --> 00:50:45,249
Ever.

1262
00:50:45,284 --> 00:50:47,567
Long time ago I did,

1263
00:50:47,602 --> 00:50:49,815
like most people.

1264
00:50:49,850 --> 00:50:51,651
Some just never get over it.

1265
00:50:51,686 --> 00:50:53,050
Do you believe in God?

1266
00:50:54,150 --> 00:50:55,915
As Laplace said,

1267
00:50:55,950 --> 00:50:58,584
"I have no need of that hypothesis."

1268
00:50:58,619 --> 00:51:00,115
He may be around, though.

1269
00:51:00,150 --> 00:51:02,800
He's everywhere. We just can't see him.

1270
00:51:02,835 --> 00:51:05,451
Pfft. If this was the best I could do,

1271
00:51:05,486 --> 00:51:07,001
I'd be hiding, too.

1272
00:51:07,036 --> 00:51:08,482
And creation...

1273
00:51:08,517 --> 00:51:10,850
It's here.
- I'm not so sure it was created.

1274
00:51:10,885 --> 00:51:12,182
What then?

1275
00:51:12,217 --> 00:51:15,783
Maybe it's just accumulated,
fields affecting fields.

1276
00:51:15,818 --> 00:51:18,451
What about the source
of the field energies?

1277
00:51:18,486 --> 00:51:20,416
Wouldn't that imply a prime mover?

1278
00:51:20,451 --> 00:51:22,549
I'd wonder about the
source of the prime mover,

1279
00:51:22,584 --> 00:51:25,783
infinite regress, but that
doesn't imply anything to me.

1280
00:51:25,818 --> 00:51:27,549
Back to the mystery.

1281
00:51:27,584 --> 00:51:29,616
It's a very old question,

1282
00:51:29,651 --> 00:51:33,517
But there's no answer
except in religious terms.

1283
00:51:33,552 --> 00:51:36,249
If you have faith, it's answered.

1284
00:51:36,284 --> 00:51:39,718
Did you ever meet any person
from our religious history?

1285
00:51:39,753 --> 00:51:41,783
A biblical figure?

1286
00:51:41,818 --> 00:51:43,117
In a way.

1287
00:51:43,152 --> 00:51:44,815
Who?

1288
00:51:44,850 --> 00:51:46,316
We should skip this one.

1289
00:51:46,351 --> 00:51:48,050
No, no, no skipping. Come on.

1290
00:51:48,085 --> 00:51:49,301
Next question.

1291
00:51:49,336 --> 00:51:50,710
No, come on!

1292
00:51:52,084 --> 00:51:53,349
Come on, spit it out!

1293
00:51:53,384 --> 00:51:55,015
Good lord! You were one of them!

1294
00:51:55,050 --> 00:51:58,684
This is going in a direction
that I didn't expect.

1295
00:51:58,719 --> 00:52:01,901
I hoped it wouldn't.
We... call it a night.

1296
00:52:01,936 --> 00:52:05,084
Come on! You were someone
in religious history?

1297
00:52:05,119 --> 00:52:06,316
Yes.

1298
00:52:06,351 --> 00:52:07,883
In the Bible?

1299
00:52:07,918 --> 00:52:08,848
Yes.

1300
00:52:08,883 --> 00:52:09,915
Someone we know?

1301
00:52:09,950 --> 00:52:11,984
How could we not know
someone in the Bible?

1302
00:52:12,019 --> 00:52:13,451
I mean somebody important.

1303
00:52:13,486 --> 00:52:14,883
You may think you know him,

1304
00:52:14,918 --> 00:52:16,416
but it's mostly myth.

1305
00:52:16,451 --> 00:52:19,800
The entire Bible is
mostly myth and allegory

1306
00:52:19,835 --> 00:52:23,150
with maybe some basis
in historical events.

1307
00:52:23,185 --> 00:52:27,484
You were part of that history?

1308
00:52:27,519 --> 00:52:28,584
Yes.

1309
00:52:29,718 --> 00:52:30,949
Moses.

1310
00:52:30,984 --> 00:52:34,817
